eval("__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);\n/* harmony export */ __webpack_require__.d(__webpack_exports__, {\n/* harmony export */   cLesson16: () => (/* binding */ cLesson16)\n/* harmony export */ });\nconst cLesson16 = {\n    id: 16,\n    title: \"Building a Real-World Mini Project\",\n    description: \"Apply everything you have learned to build a complete application.\",\n    difficulty: \"Advanced\",\n    duration: \"45 mins\",\n    content: `\r\n## Capstone Mini Project\r\n\r\nThe absolute best way to cement your knowledge in C is to build something from scratch without relying heavily on tutorials. This final lesson presents a challenge.\r\n\r\n### Project Challenge: Task Management System / API\r\nWe challenge you to build a complete CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) application.\r\n\r\n#### Requirements:\r\n1. **Core Logic**: Users should be able to create new tasks, view existing ones, update their status (e.g., *Pending* to *Completed*), and delete tasks.\r\n2. **Data Persistence**: Depending on the language, this could mean writing to a local CSV/JSON file, or integrating with a SQL/NoSQL database.\r\n3. **Input Validation**: Ensure that task titles cannot be empty and that dates are reasonably formatted. Throw and handle exceptions correctly.\r\n4. **Modular Architecture**: Do not put all your code in one file. Separate your data access layer, your business logic, and your presentation/UI layer.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Implement:\r\n- **Step 1:** Setup your environment and plan your data structures (or database schemas).\r\n- **Step 2:** Write the core functions/methods for CRUD operations.\r\n- **Step 3:** Implement the user interface or API routing to interact with those functions.\r\n- **Step 4:** Add error handling, logging, and test your code against edge cases.\r\n\r\n### Next Steps in Your Journey\r\nCongratulations on making it this far! From here, contribute to open-source projects, read other people's code on GitHub, and never stop learning. Code everyday, and you'll master C in no time!\r\n`\n};\n//# sourceURL=[module]\n//# sourceMappingURL=data:application/json;charset=utf-8;base64,\n//# sourceURL=webpack-internal:///(ssr)/./src/utils/learncourses/c/cLesson16.js\n");

